# Project Summary: Video Repurpose Engine

The Video Repurpose Engine was developed as part of an internship learning program.  
It focuses on transforming long-form video content into short clips, highlights, and summaries for reuse across platforms.

### Objectives
- Automate video repurposing
- Improve efficiency in content creation
- Enable multi-platform publishing

### Approach
- Literature review of existing video processing tools
- Workflow design using OpenCV and FFmpeg
- Team collaboration for research and documentation

### Outcomes
- A detailed report documenting methods, challenges, and future scope
- Proposed architecture for a scalable video repurposing system
